  "texts": [
    "Authorship, as a modern phenomenon, reflects the specific way of distinguishing the environment through the structural coupling between social systems, individuals, and technology.",
    "To put it simply, technological interventions and individual contributions are not new to publishing or authorship.",
    "Instead, the very conditions in which each system responds to the others in the complex eco-systemic setting create the impression of exclusivity and the need to ontologize the conditions of the present.",
    "Therefore, it is easy to conclude that technological developments are revolutionary and problematic today, while the past is seen as already determined and resolved.",
    "However, what continues is the same process of autopoiesis within the presented structural coupling, which de-ontologizes our perspective on scientific authorship."
  ],
